node.text:
The new residential Mega Yacht ‘Somnio’ will be the largest yacht in the world when it launches in 2024. 🔥 You can check how to get your photos promoted in our account, use the link in our bio @explorationfervor

This 728 feet mansion will have 39 apartments across 6 floors, with apartment prices starting from $11,000,000 with an invite only to purchase. The cost of the project is to be around $600,000,000 and it will be built in Norway. 🛥

📷 @winchdesign_wd
📍Monte-Carlo, Monaco

node.text:
Tag someone you'd like to be in Petra with 👇 Wanna see your pictures posted in our account? Apply for a feature on explorationfervor.com (link in my bio: @explorationfervor)

Petra is a site at the intersection of natural and cultural heritage forming a unique cultural landscape. Ever since Johann Ludwig Burckhardt aka Sheikh Ibrahim had re-discovered the ruin city in Petra, Jordan, in 1812, the cultural heritage site has attracted different people who shared an interest in the ancient history and culture of the Nabataeans such as travellers, pilgrims, painters and savants. However, it was not until the late 19th century that the ruins were systematically approached by archaeological researchers.

The Ancient city of Petra in Jordan is estimated to be built as early as 5th century BC. Famous for its rock-cut architecture and water conduit system, it is also called the 'Rose City' because of the colour of the stone from which it is carved. It has been a UNESCO World Heritage Site since 1985. In 2001 was added as one of the New 7 Wonders of the World.

Who would you visit this Wonder of the World with? 🤯

📽 @visualsofjulius
📍Petra, Jordan
🎶 Angles - The XX
